##### General
* Use the Generic Stepper when you want to provide the user with a general sense of the number of steps in a flow as well as where they are within that flow. This component is intended to be ancillary to the rest of the goals on the page, and as such it is intentionally scaled back in terms of functionality.
* For large and extra large screens, the Generic Stepper should display in line with the Page Title, aligned to the right side of the content area.
* For small and medium screens, the Generic Stepper will wrap directly underneath the Page Title, and will be displayed on its own line.
{{/ markdown}}
